args: Is something the matter, Cecile?\nYou seem more down than usual.
Is it really okay for me to be here?
Of course. Why would it not be?
Because I swore to regain whatever\nchivalry was still in my heart after I\nmet you again, and I haven't.
I can't serve the prince... Hell, I can't even\nfind a hint of my old optimism.
I thought for sure I could change and go\nback to being my old, useful self, but...
Ooo! You wish to be your old self again?!

Did I startle you? Wheeee hee hee ha hoo!
Yes, so sorry about that. I just heard some
people talking over here and couldn't seem
to help myself.
Clara, was it? Yes, well, I have just the\nthing to help with your worries. Behold!
One to help you sleep, yes! And while you\nslumber, it will cast a type of hypnosis\nthat lets you speak with your former self.
This sounds rather fishy. Does it have any\nside effects she should know about?
No, no! Don't worry about it! Why, I just\ntested it on myself, and I'm doing great!\nWHEEEE HEE HEE HA HA HOOOO!
Er, have you tested it on anyone else?\nBecause I cannot help but feel that you\nmay not be the best metric for—
So this hypnosis magic will let me talk to\nmy old self?
Maybe she can teach me how to be\npositive and ambitious again...
Cecile? Are you all right? You are\nmumbling to yourself.
I'll do it. I'll do it! Gimme that sweet,\nsweet hypnosis!
Ah, but that's good to hear, Cathy!\nHere you are, then! Drink up!
Thanks, weird old man! I just know this'll\nget me back to being my old self again!
Wow... I haven't felt this happy without\nmunching on a Manachew in so long!
*pant* Damnation! I'm too late.\nPerhaps I can wake her up?

Oh, I certainly wouldn't do that! It might
cause the magic to explode, you see.
Although that WOULD be fascinating...
You know what? Do it! Wheee hee hee!
My dear Cecile... Please be all right...
(I'm back at the castle in former Alberia?\nLooks like the dream medicine worked.)
(It doesn't seem like anyone can see me.\nAm I really going to be able to talk to my\nold self like this?)
Well, I suppose I should try to find myself\nfirst—and I know exactly where to look.
Heh. I'd say that's a match.
Ow. You are way too good at this, Cecile.
Oh, I don't think so. After all, Sir Raemond\nwas able to defeat a massive fiend with\nnaught but a wooden sword in his day.
That just makes me feel even more\ninferior than before...
(I mean, of course I am. All I ever did was\ntrain from sunup to sundown.)
Don't give up on me now, soldier!\nWe must always strive to be stronger\nthan we were the day before!
We must ready for any enemy who would\nseek to harm good King Aurelius!
You really are a knight among knights,\nCecile. You know that?
(I was so earnestly dedicated to the\nknight's code. And now, every word coming\nout of her mouth is a knife in my heart.)
Nope. It's just not working.\nNothing is resonating with me.
Yeesh. If you're cowering before my blade,\nyou won't have a prayer if the Other is\neventually revived.
Could you maybe say something a little\nless...terrifying?
Your terror will not keep the king safe!
Well then, what would YOU do if the\nOther came back?
Is it not obvious? I would throw myself\ninto the fray without hesitation.
Then I would save our king and protect the\nnation and its people, no matter the cost.
(Yep. Some hero you turned out to be.)
You don't know a damn thing.
Were you waiting for me to wake up, Leif?\nYou should've just let me be.
I can't have anything happening to you.\nI'm your employer, after all.
That is a relief. So then, were you able to\ndream? Did you perhaps find answers?
Yeah, but I couldn't talk to myself.
After all that build-up! Ah, well. I suppose\na dream is just a dream in the end.
All the same, we don't know if that magic\nhad any ill effects on your body, so you\nshould rest a little longer.
It's not that I couldn't talk to myself...\nIt's that I refused to.
